	<presentation id="community-service">
		<title>REST Community Service</title>
		<toc class="abstract">REST is all about designing and deploying services in a global decentralized shared space for information and services. The set of shared concepts used in this landscape is constantly evolving. One slow but important aspect of this ongoing evolution is standardization, a process that is necessarily slow, can be contentious, and requires quite a bit of energy and willingness to listen. Nevertheless, as part of the ongoing effort to make the Internet and the Web more useful for everybody, it is important that (some) members of the community participate in standardization.</toc>
		<toc class="resources"><a href="http://ietf.org/" title="Internet Engineering Task Force">IETF</a>&#160;· <a href="http://www.w3.org/" title="World Wide Web Consortium">W3C</a>&#160;· <a href="https://webconcepts.info/">Web Concepts</a></toc>
